					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">IIRC, Metroid was another example of a game that executed from NMI.  However, regularly disabling the NMI I believe is a bad idea.  Allowing recursive NMIs would be much safer (because of the partial vblank that I mentioned in my last post, it's likely to happen if you're code takes too long).  In the recursive NMI case you would just handle the vblank-related stuff, then return (based on checking if it has interrupted itself or not).</div>

